# Accessibility Audit Report

## Issues Found
1. Images missing `alt` attributes
2. Link text was generic on placeholder links
3. No `lang` attribute on `<html>` initially

## How I Fixed Them
1. Added descriptive `alt="Portrait placeholder for Juliet Adhiambo"` to all `<img>` tags
2. Changed link text from "click here" to "MDN Web Docs"
3. Added `lang="en"` to `<html>` tag on all pages
4. Used proper heading hierarchy: h1 for page title, h2 for sections
5. All form inputs have associated `<label for="">` elements

## Final Lighthouse Accessibility Score
100/100 - All accessibility audits passed
